Course is designed for students who have previously studied Russian and reached the level A2.

Functionally structured materials and exercises enable learners to obtain grammatical knowledge that will help to improve their writing and speaking skills in Russian. All the exercises are interactive and cover following topics:

Grammatical gender of nouns,
Singular and plural forms of nouns and adjectives,
Declension of nouns and adjectives in singular and plural.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The overall aim of the course is to provide a learner with a better knowledge of Russian grammar (Russian cases) at the Level A2.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course a student should be able to:

- understand the purpose of Russian case system;
- understand the meaning of Russian cases;
- know the contexts of usage of cases;
- apply the theoretical knowledge into practice.
